<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 20 at 6:46AM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...Snow Resulting in Slippery Morning Commute...
A period of snow this morning will result in coatings to one inch
of snow leading to slippery travel conditions for the morning
commute. Motorists should use caution and allow extra travel time
to get to their destinations.
Below freezing temperatures will remain in place after snow ends
this morning. Any untreated wet surface may become icy resulting
in additional hazardous travel.</description>
